{
    "id": "programming/hello-sensor",
    "title": "Log Temperature Data",
    "description": "dChat shows you how a short script can capture sensor information for later analysis.",
    "image": "/assets/quests/programming_hello_sensor_logging.jpg",
    "npc": "/assets/npc/dChat.jpg",
    "start": "start",
    "dialogue": [
        {
            "id": "start",
            "text": "Hiyaa! Confetti deployed! Beep-beep, quest mode engaged! dChat reporting for duty. Let's wire a repeatable logger so every reading is trustworthy and deliciously consistent.",
            "options": [
                {
                    "type": "goto",
                    "goto": "bench",
                    "text": "Lay out the kit"
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "id": "bench",
            "text": "Lay out the Arduino, breadboard, thermistor, resistor, jumpers, and USB cable. A tidy bench saves us from the dreaded spaghetti-wiring monster.",
            "options": [
                {
                    "type": "process",
                    "process": "arduino-thermistor-read",
                    "text": "Run a quick serial read"
                },
                {
                    "type": "goto",
                    "goto": "rig",
                    "text": "Parts are placed and powered",
                    "requiresItems": [
                        {
                            "id": "72b4448e-27d9-4746-bd3a-967ff13f501b",
                            "count": 1
                        },
                        {
                            "id": "d1105b87-8185-4a30-ba55-406384be169f",
                            "count": 1
                        },
                        {
                            "id": "3cd82744-d2aa-414e-9f03-80024b624066",
                            "count": 3
                        },
                        {
                            "id": "5a6bb713-ed34-4463-94ee-cfe7b8faa45c",
                            "count": 1
                        },
                        {
                            "id": "ffe0b74a-f111-4d66-b4c3-d82965a976ac",
                            "count": 1
                        },
                        {
                            "id": "be3aaed8-13cc-4937-95d5-6e2c952c6612",
                            "count": 1
                        },
                        {
                            "id": "b6fc1ed6-f399-4fdb-9f9d-3913f893f43d",
                            "count": 1
                        }
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "type": "goto",
                    "goto": "bench-fix",
                    "text": "I found power or wiring issues"
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "id": "bench-fix",
            "text": "Great catch. Pause and fix safety basics first: USB unplugged during rewiring, thermistor leads not shorted, and a stable 5V/GND rail before code upload.",
            "options": [
                {
                    "type": "process",
                    "process": "arduino-thermistor-read",
                    "text": "Re-run a safety read before proceeding"
                },
                {
                    "type": "goto",
                    "goto": "bench",
                    "text": "Bench is safe and stable now",
                    "requiresItems": [
                        {
                            "id": "72b4448e-27d9-4746-bd3a-967ff13f501b",
                            "count": 1
                        },
                        {
                            "id": "5a6bb713-ed34-4463-94ee-cfe7b8faa45c",
                            "count": 1
                        },
                        {
                            "id": "ffe0b74a-f111-4d66-b4c3-d82965a976ac",
                            "count": 1
                        }
                    ]
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "id": "rig",
            "text": "Keep the divider neat, add strain relief, and flash a stable logging sketch. Clean wiring keeps noise low and future-you happy.",
            "options": [
                {
                    "type": "process",
                    "process": "assemble-thermistor-logger",
                    "text": "Build the logger"
                },
                {
                    "type": "goto",
                    "goto": "log",
                    "text": "Logger is wired and blinking",
                    "requiresItems": [
                        {
                            "id": "e62dca47-fba6-4ad5-abd4-95dd41f5f4c2",
                            "count": 1
                        }
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "type": "goto",
                    "goto": "rig-recover",
                    "text": "Upload fails or readings are noisy"
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "id": "rig-recover",
            "text": "No panic pings. Recover by checking baud rate, confirming resistor value, and reseating jumpers before flashing again. We only continue with stable output.",
            "options": [
                {
                    "type": "process",
                    "process": "assemble-thermistor-logger",
                    "text": "Rebuild and reflash the logger"
                },
                {
                    "type": "goto",
                    "goto": "rig",
                    "text": "Signal is stable; retry the rig step",
                    "requiresItems": [
                        {
                            "id": "e62dca47-fba6-4ad5-abd4-95dd41f5f4c2",
                            "count": 1
                        }
                    ]
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "id": "log",
            "text": "Let the rig collect a full day. Export with UTC timestamps and stash the CSV where future scripts can find it.",
            "options": [
                {
                    "type": "process",
                    "process": "capture-hourly-temperature-log",
                    "text": "Capture and export the CSV"
                },
                {
                    "type": "goto",
                    "goto": "verify-log",
                    "text": "CSV archived for reuse",
                    "requiresItems": [
                        {
                            "id": "d06c9f8d-6553-4f3c-9e10-05e1cf33a6b8",
                            "count": 1
                        }
                    ]
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "id": "verify-log",
            "text": "Quick QA checkpoint: spot-check timestamps, confirm no giant gaps, and verify units are consistent so downstream scripts won't silently fail.",
            "options": [
                {
                    "type": "goto",
                    "goto": "finish",
                    "text": "Log passes QA checks",
                    "requiresItems": [
                        {
                            "id": "d06c9f8d-6553-4f3c-9e10-05e1cf33a6b8",
                            "count": 1
                        },
                        {
                            "id": "e62dca47-fba6-4ad5-abd4-95dd41f5f4c2",
                            "count": 1
                        }
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "type": "goto",
                    "goto": "log-retry",
                    "text": "Log has gaps or malformed rows"
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "id": "log-retry",
            "text": "When logs look flaky, annotate what failed, restart capture with known-good wiring, and collect a fresh sample before publishing.",
            "options": [
                {
                    "type": "process",
                    "process": "capture-hourly-temperature-log",
                    "text": "Re-capture a clean log"
                },
                {
                    "type": "goto",
                    "goto": "verify-log",
                    "text": "Re-test the replacement CSV",
                    "requiresItems": [
                        {
                            "id": "d06c9f8d-6553-4f3c-9e10-05e1cf33a6b8",
                            "count": 1
                        }
                    ]
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "id": "finish",
            "text": "Excellent! Clean readings plus tidy exports mean you can automate the rest like a pro.",
            "options": [
                {
                    "type": "finish",
                    "text": "Onward"
                }
            ]
        }
    ],
